Open Retail

	Philosophy

		-
			Open retail is the practice of running a for-profit consumer-oriented business by
			providing all goods and services on a "pay-what-you-want" basis.
		-

	Principles

		Automation

			-
				Open retail may be a viable business model for fully automated businesses.
			-

		Incentives

			-
				Certain businesses may operate on a hybrid model, where voluntary payments may
				count towards certain exclusive goods, services, or influence.
			-